sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client / KServe Proxy
    participant MM1 as ModelMesh Instance A<br/>8033/TCP gRPC<br/>Optional TLS/mTLS
    participant etcd as etcd Cluster<br/>2379/TCP gRPC<br/>Optional TLS
    participant MM2 as ModelMesh Instance B<br/>8033/TCP Thrift/gRPC<br/>TLS/mTLS
    participant RT1 as Model Runtime A<br/>8085/TCP or UDS<br/>No TLS (localhost)
    participant RT2 as Model Runtime B<br/>8085/TCP or UDS<br/>No TLS (localhost)

    Note over Client,RT2: Flow 1: Model Inference Request (model loaded locally)

    Client->>MM1: gRPC inference request<br/>8033/TCP, TLS optional, mTLS optional
    MM1->>etcd: Lookup model location<br/>2379/TCP, gRPC, TLS optional
    etcd-->>MM1: Model record (loaded on Instance A)
    MM1->>RT1: Forward to local runtime<br/>8085/TCP or UDS, no encryption
    RT1-->>MM1: Inference result
    MM1-->>Client: gRPC response

    Note over Client,RT2: Flow 1b: Model Inference Request (model loaded remotely)

    Client->>MM1: gRPC inference request<br/>8033/TCP
    MM1->>etcd: Lookup model location<br/>2379/TCP
    etcd-->>MM1: Model record (loaded on Instance B)
    MM1->>MM2: Forward inference via litelinks<br/>8033/TCP, Thrift/gRPC, TLS, mTLS
    MM2->>RT2: Forward to local runtime<br/>8085/TCP or UDS, no encryption
    RT2-->>MM2: Inference result
    MM2-->>MM1: Response via litelinks
    MM1-->>Client: gRPC response

    Note over Client,RT2: Flow 2: Model Registration and Loading

    Client->>MM1: registerModel gRPC<br/>8033/TCP, TLS/mTLS
    MM1->>etcd: Create model record<br/>2379/TCP, TLS
    Note over MM1: Leader selects target instance
    MM1->>RT1: loadModel gRPC<br/>8085/TCP or UDS
    RT1-->>MM1: Model loaded (size, max concurrency)
    MM1->>etcd: Update model status = LOADED<br/>2379/TCP

    Note over Client,RT2: Flow 3: Model Eviction (LRU Cache Pressure)

    Note over MM1: Cache capacity exceeded
    MM1->>RT1: unloadModel gRPC<br/>8085/TCP or UDS
    RT1-->>MM1: Model unloaded
    MM1->>etcd: Update model record<br/>2379/TCP
